SEQUENCE :
---------------

--> A Sequence is a database object that automatically generates a series of unique numbers.
--> Sequences are useful for generating values for primary keys 
--> Sequences can used with help of NEXTVAL

SYNTAX:
-----------
CREATE SEQUENCE sequence_name
[START WITH number]       -- First number of the sequence
[INCREMENT BY number]     -- Step value (default 1)
[MAXVALUE number | NOMAXVALUE]  -- Maximum value
[MINVALUE number | NOMINVALUE]  -- Minimum value
[CYCLE | NOCYCLE]         -- Reuse when limit is reached or not
[CACHE number | NOCACHE]; -- Number of sequence values cached in memory
*************************************
ðŸ”¹ How to use a Sequence
ðŸ”¹ Get the next value:
SELECT sequence_name.NEXTVAL FROM dual;
ðŸ”¹ Get the current value:
SELECT sequence_name.CURRVAL FROM dual;

